    },
    {
        "_id": "69a8ea5053e250fdaf139d6f",
        "name": "MazeCow",
        "adjectives": [
            "alpha male",
            "sigma",
            "skibidy"
        ],
        "body": {
            "head": "brown",
            "frontLeft": "brown",
            "frontRight": "brown",
            "rearLeft": "brown",
            "rearRight": "brown",
            "_id": "69b2acb25ddac37686700503"
        },
        "derpy": false,
        "bio": "Mazecow is the kind of duck that walks into a pond like it already owns the place. A true sigma, Mazecow doesn\u2019t follow the flock\u2019s drama or noise \u2014 it moves on its own path, calmly observing everything while quietly solving problems no one else even noticed. When the other ducks panic about which way to swim, Mazecow has already mapped the maze of lily pads and is three turns ahead. \nDespite that independent vibe, Mazecow still has undeniable alpha male energy. Confident, bold, and never backing down from a challenge, Mazecow naturally ends up leading the group through tricky waters and weird classroom adventures alike. Other ducks might try to copy the swagger, but Mazecow makes it look effortless. \nAnd of course, there\u2019s the skibidy factor. Mazecow has a goofy side that shows up at the most unexpected times \u2014 dancing across the pond, making bizarre quacking noises, or pulling off chaotic moves that somehow still work perfectly. One moment Mazecow is calculating the smartest path forward, and the next it\u2019s doing something so ridiculous the whole flock can\u2019t stop laughing. Sigma mind. \nAlpha confidence. Skibidy chaos. That\u2019s Mazecow.",
        "date": {
            "$date": "2026-03-04T00:00:00Z"
        },
        "approved": true,
        "stats": {
            "strength": 10,
            "health": 0,
            "focus": 10,
            "intelligence": 10,
            "kindness": 0,
            "_id": "69b2acb25ddac37686700504"
        },
        "__v": 0,
        "assembler": "Isaac Trost"
